cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the implementation of access control lists and service level agreements to secure a network for business-to-business applications. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). The paper also discusses techniques and methodologies to reduce attacks and vulnerabilities, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The paper may also touch upon distributed systems (cs.DC) and system security (cs.SI) as it discusses the location and techniques used in attacks.
